The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the World Summit in Defense of Persecuted Christians. He expressed his gratitude to Reverend Franklin Graham for organizing the event and emphasized the importance of defending Christians and all those who suffer for their beliefs. Pence spoke about the persecution faced by Christians around the world, particularly in the Middle East, and condemned the acts of radical Islamic terrorists, including ISIS. He highlighted the decline of Christian populations in countries like Iraq and Syria and pledged the commitment of the Trump administration to bring relief and comfort to believers. Pence also emphasized the importance of religious freedom and stated that protecting and promoting religious freedom is a foreign policy priority of the Trump administration. He concluded his speech by encouraging believers to cling to one another and have confidence in God's plans for them.